Package com.example.parking_garage_management

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CarLotIsFull
    CarLotIsFull is a class that displays a dialog box that is used to inform user when the car lot is full upon a park attempt.
    Create_Account_Activity
    Screen allows user to create a new account
    DisplayReceipt
    DisplayReceipt displays a dialog box with the retrieved vehicle's info along with the total amount due
    DisplayTicket
    DisplayTicket displays a dialog box with the parked vehicle's info
    ExampleInstrumentedTest
    Instrumented test, which will execute on an Android device.
    ExampleUnitTest
    Example local unit test, which will execute on the development machine (host).
    MainActivity
    Log in screen of the application
    MotorcycleLotIsFull
    MotorcycleLotIsFull is a class that displays a dialog box that is used to inform user when the motorcycle lot is full upon a park attempt.
    Park_Or_Retrieve_Activity
    Allows user to park or retrieve vehicle by selecting the vehicle type and entering license plate number
    ParkingGarageManager
    Parking garage manager manages and assigns parking spaces as well as calculates the amount due upon retrieval
    TruckLotIsFull
    TruckLotIsFull is a class that displays a dialog box that is used to inform user when the truck lot is full upon a park attempt.
    UserAccount
    UserAccount facilitates the process of creating a new user account
    Vehicle
    Vehicle class is used to create vehicles and assign information to them associated with the vehicle and its activities
    VehicleAlreadyParked
    Class displays a dialog box that is used to inform user when a vehicle has already been parked if the user enters the same license number twice.
    VehicleNotFound
    Class displays a dialog box that is used to inform user the wrong license number has been entered in an retrieval attempt
    WrongPassWord
    Class displays a dialog box that informs user that the password entered is incorrect
    WrongPassWordFormat
    Class displays a dialog box that is used to inform user when the password created does not meet criteria
    WrongUserName
    Class displays a dialog box that is used to inform user when the user name that is entered during log in is incorrect
